:<font size="15">אנושׁ</font></div>

===Pronunciation===
אנושׁ / 'ĕnôsh / en-oshe'

===Etymology===
From {{HH|605}}; 

 their age, husband, (certain, mortal) man, people, person, servant, some (X of them), + stranger, those, + their trade. It is often unexpressed in the Engl. version, especially when used in apposition with another word. Compare {{HH|376}}.

